name: lib/gulp-graph.js
GulpGraph
description:
The GulpGraph is the child implementation that contains the actual AST parsing
logic for initialization

name: assemblegraph
description: Assembles the initial graph from the source JavaScript gulpfile

name: defineTask
description: Function to initially define a task when reading from JavaScript string

params.name: task_name
params.description: the name of the task to define

params.name: task_ast
params.description: tree of the task's function, if it calls one, else null

name: defineSubTask
description: TODO: Function that assembles the graph of the gulp task's sub routines

params.name: parent
params.description: the gulp task that the subroutine belongs to

name: lib/gulp-nodes.js
lib/interface.js
JointGraph
description:
the JointGraph interface is intended as an abstract class for
the GulpGraph to inherit

name: constructor
description:
The JointGraph wraps a graphlib object, a js string,
a dependencies array, and a config object

name: GulpNode
description:
the GulpNode interface is intended as an abstract class for
the GulpGraph Nodes to inherit

name: constructor
description:
The GulpNode is constructed from an object, allowing its child classes
to have different initialization properties. Requires a name, defaults
type to 'GulpNode'

name: addSelf
description:
used by some children classes to add themselves to the JointGraph.GRAPH
at the end of initialization.

params.name: graph
params.description: the parent graph for the node to add itself to
